    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe vertical split line inconsistently splits statuslines depending on whether the windows are at the bottom:\n<img width=\"179\" height=\"138\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b3810f85-dc25-4cc4-9a21-1fbc181af081\" />\nIt seems that it would be more consistent if the split line passed all the way down through the status line.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nOpen nvim and create vertical splits, each with horizontal splits.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect consistency.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI assume vim behaves the same.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nTerminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256\n\n### Installation\n\nchoco install neovim",
